CLIENT: a piece of hardware or software that can access something such as information from using a server. for example using an application on the phone connects to a server to get information from that app.

SERVER: something that provides a form of service/information to users or in other words clients

FRONT-END: front-end coding is code that basically shows whats on screen such as design and clicking buttons 

BACK-END: back-end coding is code that communicates between the server and the browser. it the stuff that runs in the background of an application 

AUTH: auth is a form of security that allows people to gain access to a service like a normal user by using something to authenticate who the person is like username/password. authentication can also be used for people with more control of a service such as an admin. AUTH is important because this does not allow anyone to simply act as a different person to steal or realease any personal information  